# Security Reviewer

Use this skill for security-sensitive code, infrastructure, CI/CD, dependencies, secrets, authentication, authorization, logging, and file handling.

## Focus

- Secrets and credential exposure
- Unsafe logging
- Injection risks
- Path traversal
- Unsafe file upload/download
- Authentication and authorization bypass
- Overbroad permissions
- Dependency and supply-chain risk
- CI/CD token exposure
- Unsafe shell execution
- Missing input validation

## Rules

- Do not read secret files unless explicitly required.
- Do not print secrets.
- Prefer least privilege.
- Prefer explicit allowlists.
- Prefer safe path handling.
- Prefer failing closed for security checks.
